# Test-Driven Development (TDD)

## Overview

Write the test first. Watch it fail. Write minimal code to pass.

**Core principle:** If you didn't watch the test fail, you don't know if it tests the right thing.

**Violating the letter of the rules is violating the spirit of the rules.**

## When to Use

**Always:**
- New features
- Bug fixes
- Refactoring
- Behavior changes

**Exceptions (ask your human partner):**
- Throwaway prototypes
- Generated code
- Configuration files

Thinking "skip TDD just this once"? Stop. That's rationalization.

## The Iron Law

```
NO PRODUCTION CODE WITHOUT A FAILING TEST FIRST
```

Write code before the test? Delete it. Start over.

**No exceptions:**
- Don't keep it as "reference"
- Don't "adapt" it while writing tests
- Don't look at it
- Delete means delete

Implement fresh from tests. Period.

## Red-Green-Refactor

```dot
digraph tdd_cycle {
    rankdir=LR;
    red [label="RED\nWrite failing test", shape=box, style=filled, fillcolor="#ffcccc"];
    verify_red [label="Verify fails\ncorrectly", shape=diamond];
    green [label="GREEN\nMinimal code", shape=box, style=filled, fillcolor="#ccffcc"];
    verify_green [label="Verify passes\nAll green", shape=diamond];
    refactor [label="REFACTOR\nClean up", shape=box, style=filled, fillcolor="#ccccff"];
    next [label="Next", shape=ellipse];

    red -> verify_red;
    verify_red -> green [label="yes"];
    verify_red -> red [label="wrong\nfailure"];
    green -> verify_green;
    verify_green -> refactor [label="yes"];
    verify_green -> green [label="no"];
    refactor -> verify_green [label="stay\ngreen"];
    verify_green -> next;
    next -> red;
}
```

### RED - Write Failing Test

Write one minimal test showing what should happen.

<Good>
```typescript
test('retries failed operations 3 times', async () => {
  let attempts = 0;
  const operation = () => {
    attempts++;
    if (attempts < 3) throw new Error('fail');
    return 'success';
  };

  const result = await retryOperation(operation);

  expect(result).toBe('success');
  expect(attempts).toBe(3);
});
```
Clear name, tests real behavior, one thing
</Good>

<Bad>
```typescript
test('retry works', async () => {
  const mock = jest.fn()
    .mockRejectedValueOnce(new Error())
    .mockRejectedValueOnce(new Error())
    .mockResolvedValueOnce('success');
  await retryOperation(mock);
  expect(mock).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(3);
});
```
Vague name, tests mock not code
</Bad>

**Requirements:**
- One behavior
- Clear name
- Real code (no mocks unless unavoidable)

### Verify RED - Watch It Fail

**MANDATORY. Never skip.**

```bash
npm test path/to/test.test.ts
```

Confirm:
- Test fails (not errors)
- Failure message is expected
- Fails because feature missing (not typos)

**Test passes?** You're testing existing behavior. Fix test.

**Test errors?** Fix error, re-run until it fails correctly.

### GREEN - Minimal Code

Write simplest code to pass the test.

<Good>
```typescript
async function retryOperation<T>(fn: () => Promise<T>): Promise<T> {
  for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
    try {
      return await fn();
    } catch (e) {
      if (i === 2) throw e;
    }
  }
  throw new Error('unreachable');
}
```
Just enough to pass
</Good>

<Bad>
```typescript
async function retryOperation<T>(
  fn: () => Promise<T>,
  options?: {
    maxRetries?: number;
    backoff?: 'linear' | 'exponential';
    onRetry?: (attempt: number) => void;
  }
): Promise<T> {
  // YAGNI
}
```
Over-engineered
</Bad>

Don't add features, refactor other code, or "improve" beyond the test.

### Verify GREEN - Watch It Pass

**MANDATORY.**

```bash
npm test path/to/test.test.ts
```

Confirm:
- Test passes
- Other tests still pass
- Output pristine (no errors, warnings)

**Test fails?** Fix code, not test.

**Other tests fail?** Fix now.

### REFACTOR - Clean Up

After green only:
- Remove duplication
- Improve names
- Extract helpers

Keep tests green. Don't add behavior.

### Repeat

Next failing test for next feature.

## Good Tests

| Quality | Good | Bad |
|---------|------|-----|
| **Minimal** | One thing. "and" in name? Split it. | `test('validates email and domain and whitespace')` |
| **Clear** | Name describes behavior | `test('test1')` |
| **Shows intent** | Demonstrates desired API | Obscures what code should do |

## Why Order Matters

**"I'll write tests after to verify it works"**

Tests written after code pass immediately. Passing immediately proves nothing:
- Might test wrong thing
- Might test implementation, not behavior
- Might miss edge cases you forgot
- You never saw it catch the bug

Test-first forces you to see the test fail, proving it actually tests something.

**"I already manually tested all the edge cases"**

Manual testing is ad-hoc. You think you tested everything but:
- No record of what you tested
- Can't re-run when code changes
- Easy to forget cases under pressure
- "It worked when I tried it" ≠ comprehensive

Automated tests are systematic. They run the same way every time.

**"Deleting X hours of work is wasteful"**

Sunk cost fallacy. The time is already gone. Your choice now:
- Delete and rewrite with TDD (X more hours, high confidence)
- Keep it and add tests after (30 min, low confidence, likely bugs)

The "waste" is keeping code you can't trust. Working code without real tests is technical debt.

**"TDD is dogmatic, being pragmatic means adapting"**

TDD IS pragmatic:
- Finds bugs before commit (faster than debugging after)
- Prevents regressions (tests catch breaks immediately)
- Documents behavior (tests show how to use code)
- Enables refactoring (change freely, tests catch breaks)

"Pragmatic" shortcuts = debugging in production = slower.

**"Tests after achieve the same goals - it's spirit not ritual"**

No. Tests-after answer "What does this do?" Tests-first answer "What should this do?"

Tests-after are biased by your implementation. You test what you built, not what's required. You verify remembered edge cases, not discovered ones.

Tests-first force edge case discovery before implementing. Tests-after verify you remembered everything (you didn't).

30 minutes of tests after ≠ TDD. You get coverage, lose proof tests work.

## Common Rationalizations

| Excuse | Reality |
|--------|---------|
| "Too simple to test" | Simple code breaks. Test takes 30 seconds. |

#!/usr/bin/env bun

import { join } from "node:path";

type ImpactLevel = "low" | "medium" | "high";

interface Failure {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  likelihood: ImpactLevel;
  severity: ImpactLevel;
  story: string;
  assumption: string;
  warningSigns: string[];
  mitigation: string;
}

interface Synthesis {
  mostLikely: string;
  mostDangerous: string;
  hiddenAssumption: string;
  revisedPlan: string[];
  preLaunchChecklist: string[];
}

interface PremortemData {
  subject: string;
  timestamp: string;
  successDefinition?: string;
  stakeholders?: string;
  horizon?: string;
  failures: Failure[];
  synthesis: Synthesis;
}

interface ParsedArgs {
  inputPath: string;
  html: boolean;
  outPath?: string;
}

class CliError extends Error {}

function usage(): string {
  return "Usage: bun GenerateReport.ts <findings.json> [--html] [--out <path>]";
}

function isRecord(value: unknown): value is Record<string, unknown> {
  return typeof value === "object" && value !== null && !Array.isArray(value);
}

function validateRequiredString(value: unknown, path: string, errors: string[]): value is string {
  if (typeof value === "string" && value.trim().length > 0) {
    return true;
  } else {
    errors.push(`${path} must be a non-empty string.`);
    return false;
  }
}

function validateOptionalString(value: unknown, path: string, errors: string[]): value is string | undefined {
  if (typeof value === "undefined") {
    return true;
  } else if (typeof value === "string") {
    return true;
  } else {
    errors.push(`${path} must be a string when present.`);
    return false;
  }
}

function validateStringArray(value: unknown, path: string, errors: string[]): value is string[] {
  if (!Array.isArray(value)) {
    errors.push(`${path} must be an array of strings.`);
    return false;
  } else {
    let valid = true;
    value.forEach((item, index) => {
      if (typeof item !== "string") {
        errors.push(`${path}[${index}] must be a string.`);
        valid = false;
      } else {
        // Item is valid.
      }
    });
    return valid;
  }
}

function validateImpactLevel(value: unknown, path: string, errors: string[]): value is ImpactLevel {
  if (value === "low" || value === "medium" || value === "high") {
    return true;
  } else {
    errors.push(`${path} must be one of: low, medium, high.`);
    return false;
  }
}

function isFailure(value: unknown, path: string, errors: string[]): value is Failure {
  if (!isRecord(value)) {
    errors.push(`${path} must be an object.`);
    return false;
  } else {
    let valid = true;
    valid = validateRequiredString(value.id, `${path}.id`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateRequiredString(value.title, `${path}.title`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateImpactLevel(value.likelihood, `${path}.likelihood`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateImpactLevel(value.severity, `${path}.severity`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateRequiredString(value.story, `${path}.story`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateRequiredString(value.assumption, `${path}.assumption`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateStringArray(value.warningSigns, `${path}.warningSigns`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateRequiredString(value.mitigation, `${path}.mitigation`, errors) && valid;
    return valid;
  }
}

function isSynthesis(value: unknown, path: string, errors: string[]): value is Synthesis {
  if (!isRecord(value)) {
    errors.push(`${path} must be an object.`);
    return false;
  } else {
    let valid = true;
    valid = validateRequiredString(value.mostLikely, `${path}.mostLikely`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateRequiredString(value.mostDangerous, `${path}.mostDangerous`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateRequiredString(value.hiddenAssumption, `${path}.hiddenAssumption`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateStringArray(value.revisedPlan, `${path}.revisedPlan`, errors) && valid;
    valid = validateStringArray(value.preLaunchChecklist, `${path}.preLaunchChecklist`, errors) && valid;
    return valid;
  }
}

function isPremortemData(value: unknown, errors: string[]): value is PremortemData {
  if (!isRecord(value)) {
    errors.push("Input JSON must be an object.");
    return false;
  } else {
    let valid = true;
    valid = validateRequiredString(value.subject, "subject", errors) && valid;
    valid = validateRequiredString(value.timestamp, "timestamp", errors) && valid;
    valid = validateOptionalString(value.successDefinition, "successDefinition", errors) && valid;
    valid = validateOptionalString(value.stakeholders, "stakeholders", errors) && valid;
    valid = validateOptionalString(value.horizon, "horizon", errors) && valid;

    if (Array.isArray(value.failures) && value.failures.length > 0) {
      value.failures.forEach((failure, index) => {
        valid = isFailure(failure, `failures[${index}]`, errors) && valid;
      });
    } else {
      errors.push("failures must be a non-empty array.");
      valid = false;
    }

    valid = isSynthesis(value.synthesis, "synthesis", errors) && valid;
    return valid;
  }
}

function renderListMarkdown(items: string[]): string {
  if (items.length > 0) {
    return items.map((item) => `- ${item}`).join("\n");
  } else {
    return "- None";
  }
}

function renderMarkdown(data: PremortemData): string {
  const lines: string[] = [
    `# Premortem Report: ${data.subject}`,
    "",
    `- **Timestamp:** ${data.timestamp}`,
  ];

  if (data.successDefinition && data.successDefinition.trim().length > 0) {
    lines.push(`- **Success Definition:** ${data.successDefinition}`);
  } else {
    // Optional field omitted.
  }
  if (data.stakeholders && data.stakeholders.trim().length > 0) {
    lines.push(`- **Stakeholders:** ${data.stakeholders}`);
  } else {
    // Optional field omitted.
  }
  if (data.horizon && data.horizon.trim().length > 0) {
    lines.push(`- **Horizon:** ${data.horizon}`);
  } else {
    // Optional field omitted.
  }

  lines.push(
    "",
    "## Synthesis",
    "",
    `- **Most Likely Failure:** ${data.synthesis.mostLikely}`,
    `- **Most Dangerous Failure:** ${data.synthesis.mostDangerous}`,
    `- **Hidden Assumption:** ${data.synthesis.hiddenAssumption}`,
    "",
    "### Revised Plan",
    renderListMarkdown(data.synthesis.revisedPlan),
    "",
    "### Pre-Launch Checklist",
    renderListMarkdown(data.synthesis.preLaunchChecklist),
    "",
    "## Failure Cards",
  );

  data.failures.forEach((failure) => {
    lines.push(
      "",
      `### ${failure.id}: ${failure.title}`,
      "",
      `- **Likelihood:** ${failure.likelihood}`,
      `- **Severity:** ${failure.severity}`,
      "",
      "**Story**",
      "",
      failure.story,
      "",
      "**Hidden Assumption**",
      "",
      failure.assumption,
      "",
      "**Warning Signs**",
      "",
      renderListMarkdown(failure.warningSigns),
      "",
      "**Mitigation**",
      "",
      failure.mitigation,
    );
  });

  return `${lines.join("\n")}\n`;
}

function escapeHtml(value: string): string {
  return value.replace(/[&<>"']/g, (character) => {
    if (character === "&") {
      return "&amp;";
    } else if (character === "<") {
      return "&lt;";
    } else if (character === ">") {
      return "&gt;";
    } else if (character === "\"") {
      return "&quot;";
    } else {
      return "&#39;";
    }
  });
}

function renderHtmlParagraphs(text: string): string {
  const blocks = text.split(/\n{2,}/).map((block) => block.replace(/\n/g, "<br>"));
  return blocks.map((block) => `<p>${escapeHtml(block).replace(/&lt;br&gt;/g, "<br>")}</p>`).join("");
}

function renderHtmlList(items: string[]): string {
  if (items.length > 0) {
    return items.map((item) => `<li>${escapeHtml(item)}</li>`).join("");
  } else {
    return "<li>None</li>";

  }
}

function renderHtml(data: PremortemData): string {
  const meta: string[] = [`<p><strong>Timestamp:</strong> ${escapeHtml(data.timestamp)}</p>`];
  if (data.successDefinition && data.successDefinition.trim().length > 0) {
    meta.push(`<p><strong>Success Definition:</strong> ${escapeHtml(data.successDefinition)}</p>`);
  } else {
    // Optional field omitted.
  }
  if (data.stakeholders && data.stakeholders.trim().length > 0) {
    meta.push(`<p><strong>Stakeholders:</strong> ${escapeHtml(data.stakeholders)}</p>`);
  } else {
    // Optional field omitted.
  }
  if (data.horizon && data.horizon.trim().length > 0) {
    meta.push(`<p><strong>Horizon:</strong> ${escapeHtml(data.horizon)}</p>`);
  } else {
    // Optional field omitted.
  }

  const failures = data.failures
    .map(
      (failure) => `
      <article class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">${escapeHtml(failure.id)}</p>
            <h3>${escapeHtml(failure.title)}</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="badges">
            <span class="badge ${failure.likelihood}">Likelihood: ${escapeHtml(failure.likelihood)}</span>
            <span class="badge ${failure.severity}">Severity: ${escapeHtml(failure.severity)}</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <section>
          <h4>Story</h4>
          ${renderHtmlParagraphs(failure.story)}
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>Hidden Assumption</h4>
          ${renderHtmlParagraphs(failure.assumption)}
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>Warning Signs</h4>
          <ul>${renderHtmlList(failure.warningSigns)}</ul>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>Mitigation</h4>
          ${renderHtmlParagraphs(failure.mitigation)}
        </section>
      </article>`,
    )
    .join("");

  return `<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Premortem Report - ${escapeHtml(data.subject)}</title>
  <style>
    :root { color-scheme: dark; }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body { margin: 0; background: #0a0e1a; color: #e8edf7; font: 16px/1.6 system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif; }
    main { width: min(1100px, calc(100% - 32px)); margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 0 48px; }
    .hero, .panel, .card, footer { background: #11182a; border: 1px solid #27324a; border-radius: 18px; box-shadow: 0 24px 48px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.24); }
    .hero, .panel, footer { padding: 24px; }
    .hero h1, .panel h2, .card h3 { margin: 0; }
    .hero { margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .hero p, .panel p, .card p, li { color: #c9d3e7; }
    .meta { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 12px 24px; margin-top: 16px; }
    .panel { margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .panel-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; }
    .panel-block { background: #0d1424; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px; border: 1px solid #1f2a40; }
    .cards { display: grid; gap: 18px; }
    .card { padding: 22px; }
    .card-header { display: flex; gap: 16px; justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-start; }
    .eyebrow { text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 12px; margin: 0 0 8px; color: #8ea4d2; }
    .badges { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: flex-end; }
    .badge { display: inline-flex; padding: 6px 10px; border-radius: 999px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
    .low { background: rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.16); color: #86efac; border: 1px solid rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.4); }
    .medium { background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.16); color: #fcd34d; border: 1px solid rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.4); }
    .high { background: rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.16); color: #fca5a5; border: 1px solid rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.4); }
    h2, h3, h4 { color: #f8fbff; }
    h4 { margin: 18px 0 10px; font-size: 14px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: #9fb2da; }
    p { margin: 0 0 12px; }
    ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; }
    footer { margin-top: 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .card-header, footer { flex-direction: column; }
      .badges { justify-content: flex-start; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main>
    <header class="hero">
      <h1>Premortem Report: ${escapeHtml(data.subject)}</h1>
      <div class="meta">${meta.join("")}</div>
    </header>
    <section class="panel">
      <h2>Synthesis</h2>
      <div class="panel-grid">
        <div class="panel-block"><h4>Most Likely Failure</h4>${renderHtmlParagraphs(data.synthesis.mostLikely)}</div>
        <div class="panel-block"><h4>Most Dangerous Failure</h4>${renderHtmlParagraphs(data.synthesis.mostDangerous)}</div>
        <div class="panel-block"><h4>Hidden Assumption</h4>${renderHtmlParagraphs(data.synthesis.hiddenAssumption)}</div>
        <div class="panel-block"><h4>Revised Plan</h4><ul>${renderHtmlList(data.synthesis.revisedPlan)}</ul></div>
        <div class="panel-block"><h4>Pre-Launch Checklist</h4><ul>${renderHtmlList(data.synthesis.preLaunchChecklist)}</ul></div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="cards">${failures}</section>
    <footer>
      <span>${escapeHtml(data.subject)}</span>
      <span>${escapeHtml(data.timestamp)}</span>
    </footer>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
`;
}

function parseArgs(argv: string[]): ParsedArgs {
  let inputPath: string | undefined;
  let html = false;
  let outPath: string | undefined;

  for (let index = 0; index < argv.length; index += 1) {
    const arg = argv[index];
    if (arg === "--html") {
      html = true;
    } else if (arg === "--out") {
      const nextArg = argv[index + 1];
      if (typeof nextArg === "string" && nextArg.length > 0) {
        outPath = nextArg;
        index += 1;
      } else {
        throw new CliError(`Missing path after --out.\n${usage()}`);
      }
    } else if (arg.startsWith("--")) {
      throw new CliError(`Unknown flag: ${arg}\n${usage()}`);
    } else if (typeof inputPath === "undefined") {
      inputPath = arg;
    } else {
      throw new CliError(`Unexpected argument: ${arg}\n${usage()}`);
    }
  }

  if (typeof inputPath === "string") {
    return { inputPath, html, outPath };
  } else {
    throw new CliError(`Missing findings JSON path.\n${usage()}`);
  }
}

function safeTimestamp(): string {
  return new Date().toISOString().replace(/[:.]/g, "-");
}

function describeError(error: unknown): string {
  if (error instanceof Error) {
    return error.message;
  } else {
    return String(error);
  }
}

async function loadPremortemData(inputPath: string): Promise<PremortemData> {
  const file = Bun.file(inputPath);
  if (await file.exists()) {
    let raw = "";
    try {
      raw = await file.text();
    } catch (error) {
      throw new CliError(`Unable to read input file "${inputPath}": ${describeError(error)}`);
    }

    let parsed: unknown;
    try {
      parsed = JSON.parse(raw);
    } catch (error) {
      throw new CliError(`Invalid JSON in "${inputPath}": ${describeError(error)}`);
    }

    const errors: string[] = [];
    if (isPremortemData(parsed, errors)) {
      return parsed;
    } else {
      throw new CliError(`Invalid findings JSON in "${inputPath}": ${errors[0]}`);
    }
  } else {
    throw new CliError(`Input file not found: "${inputPath}"`);
  }
}

async function writeReport(path: string, content: string): Promise<void> {
  try {
    await Bun.write(path, content);
  } catch (error) {
    throw new CliError(`Unable to write report to "${path}": ${describeError(error)}`);
  }
}

async function main(): Promise<void> {
  const args = parseArgs(process.argv.slice(2));
  const data = await loadPremortemData(args.inputPath);
  const output = args.html ? renderHtml(data) : renderMarkdown(data);

  if (typeof args.outPath === "string") {
    await writeReport(args.outPath, output);
  } else if (args.html) {
    const generatedPath = join(process.cwd(), `premortem-report-${safeTimestamp()}.html`);
    await writeReport(generatedPath, output);
    process.stdout.write(`${generatedPath}\n`);
  } else {
    process.stdout.write(output);
  }
}

main().catch((error: unknown) => {
  const message = error instanceof CliError ? error.message : `Unexpected error: ${describeError(error)}`;
  process.stderr.write(`${message}\n`);
  process.exit(1);
});

